==English==
===Etymology===
Sappho, a poet of the isle of [[Lesbos]] (612 BCE - 570 BCE]] + '''[[-ic]]'''

===Pronunciation===
*(''US''): /ˈsaf ɪzm/

===Noun===
Lesbianism; female homosexuality

====Connotation====
The term is somewhat archaic.  The preferred term today tends to be [[lesbianism]].

====Derived terms====
*[[sapphist]]

====Translations====
*French: [[sapphisme]], [[saphisme]]
*German: [[Sapphismus]]
*Italian: [[saffismo]]
*Portuguese: [[safismo]]
*Spanish: [[safismo]]


